ategory:Arizona Coyotes players]]\n[[Category:Edmonton Oilers players]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey people from Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey players at the 2018 Winter Olympics]]\n[[Category:Nashville Predators players]]\n[[Category:Oklahoma City Barons players]]\n[[Category:Olympic ice hockey players of the United States]]\n[[Category:People from Milford, Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Pittsburgh Penguins players]]\n[[Category:SC Bern players]]\n[[Category:Stockton Thunder players]]\n[[Category:Toronto Maple Leafs players]]\n[[Category:Toronto Marlies players]]\n[[Category:Undrafted National Hockey League players]]\n[[Category:Yale Bulldogs men's ice hockey players]]\n", "name_user": "Mandarax", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fix typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mark_Arcobello"}
{"title_page": "List of Top Country Albums number ones of 2015", "text_new": "[[File:LukeBryanApr10.jpg|thumb|180px|[[Luke Bryan]] had two number ones in 2015.]]\n[[Top Country Albums]] is a [[record chart|chart]] that ranks the top-performing [[country music]] albums in the United States, published by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''.  In 2015, 23 different albums topped the chart; placings were based on electronic [[point of sale]] data from retail outlets.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7669133/billboard-genre-album-charts-consumption-streams-track-sales|title=Billboard's Genre Album Charts Will Now Incorporate Streams & Track Sales|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=January 26, 2017|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{-}}\n==Chart history==\n[[File:Sam Hunt at C2C Festival 2014.png|thumb|upright|[[Sam Hunt]] spent eight weeks at number one with his debut album ''[[Montevallo (album)|Montevallo]]''.|alt=Singer Sam Hunt]]\n[[File:Don Henley.png |thumb|upright|alt=Singer Don Henley|[[Don Henley]] of the [[Eagles (band)|Eagles]] topped the country chart with his first solo album since 2000.]]\n[[File:Jimbo Hart and Jason Isbell.jpg|thumb|upright|alt=Singer Jason Isbell|[[Jason Isbell]] (right) achieved his first number one with ''[[Something More Than Free]]''.]]\n[[File:Darius_Rucker.jpg|thumb|upright|alt=Singer Darius Rucker|''[[Southern Style]]'' was a chart-topper for [[Darius Rucker]].]]\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n!scope=col|Issue date\n!scope=col|Title\n!scope=col|Artist(s)\n\n!scope=col class=unsortable|Ref.\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|January 3}}\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[Man Against Machine]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\"| {{sortname|Garth|Brooks}}\n| align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2015-01-03/country-albums|title=Country Albums chart for January 3, 2015|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=December 25, 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts| January 10}}\n\n| align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2015-01-10/country-albums|title=Country Albums chart for January 10, 2015|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=January 1, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts| January 17}}\n| ''[[Old Boots, New Dirt]]''\n| {{sortname|Jason|Aldean}}\n\n| align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2015-01-17/country-albums|title=Country Albums chart for January 17, 2015|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=January 8, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts| January 24}}\n| ''[[Man Against Machine]]''\n| {{sortname|Garth|Brooks}}\n\n| align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2015-01-24/country-albums|title=Country Albums chart for January 24, 2015|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=January 15, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts| January 31}}\n| rowspan=\"4\"| ''[[Montevallo (album)|Montevallo]]''\n| rowspan=\"4\"| {{sortname|Sam|Hunt}}\n\n| align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2015-01-31/country-albums|title=Country Albums chart for January 31, 2015|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=January 22, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts| February 7}}\n\n| align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2015-02-07/country-albums|title=Country Albums chart for February 7, 2015|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=January 29, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts| February 14}}\n\n| align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2015-02-14/country-albums|title=Country Albums chart for February 14, 2015|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=February 5, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts| February 21}}\n\n| align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2015-02-21/country-albums|title=Country Albums chart for February 21, 2015|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=February 12, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts| 