le:LukeBryanApr10.jpg|thumb|right|180px|[[Luke Bryan]] had two number ones in 2015.]]\n[[Top Country Albums]] is a [[record chart|chart]] that ranks the top-performing [[country music]] albums in the United States, published by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''.  In 2015, 23 different albums topped the chart; placings were based on electronic [[point of sale]] data from retail outlets.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7669133/billboard-genre-album-charts-consumption-streams-track-sales|title=Billboard's Genre Album Charts Will Now Incorporate Streams & Track Sales|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=January 26, 2017|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{-}}\n==Chart history==\n[[File:Sam Hunt at C2C Festival 2014.png|thumb|right|upright|[[Sam Hunt]] spent eight weeks at number one with his debut album ''[[Montevallo (album)|Montevallo]]''.|alt=Singer Sam Hunt]]\n[[File:Don Henley.png |thumb|right|upright|alt=Singer Don Henley|[[Don Henley]] of the [[Eagles (band)|Eagles]] topped the country chart with his first solo album since 2000.]]\n[[File:Jimbo Hart and Jason Isbell.jpg|thumb|right|upright|alt=Singer Jason Isbell|[[Jason Isbell]] (right) achieved his first number one with ''[[Something More Than Free]]''.]]\n[[File:Darius_Rucker.jpg|thumb|right|upright|alt=Singer Darius Rucker|''[[Southern Style]]'' was a chart-topper for [[Darius Rucker]].]]\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n!scope=col|Issue date\n!scope=col|Title\n!scope=col|Artist(s)\n\n!scope=col class=unsortable|Ref.\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|January 3}}\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[Man Against Machine]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\"| {{sortname|Garth|Brooks}}\n| align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2015-01-03/country-albums|title=Country Albums chart for January 3, 2015|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=December 25, 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts| January 10}}\n\n| align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.b